	     Pretoria - A 21-year-old man has handed himself to police after a local businessman was found dead at a tavern in Refilwe, Cullinan, Gauteng police say. The man allegedly stabbed his 31-year-old victim during an altercation over a girlfriend in the early hours of Saturday morning, Constable Connie Moganedi said. The suspect turned himself in at 08:30 on Saturday. The victim's body showed he had also sustained head injuries. His body was taken to Bronkhorstspruit mortuary. The suspect will appear in the Cullinan Magistrate's Court soon, Moganedi added. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  